  "id": "019d286c-c8e3-7462-a4e5-a49e274ccdc1",
  "content": "e — clone because fallback branch also needs these values:\nlet opts = corvia_kernel::rag_types::RetrievalOpts {\n    limit,\n    expand_graph: false,\n    content_role: content_role.clone(),\n    source_origin: source_origin.clone(),\n    ..Default::default()\n};\n```\n\nFor the fallback raw store search path, apply post-filter after results:\n\n```rust\n// Fallback: raw store search\nlet search_limit = if content_role.is_some() || source_origin.is_some() {\n    limit * 3\n} else {\n    limit\n};\nlet results = state.store.search(&embedding, scope_id, search_limit).await\n    .map_err(|e| (INTERNAL_ERROR, format!(\"Search failed: {e}\")))?;\nlet results = corvia_kernel::retriever::post_filter_metadata(\n    results,\n    content_role.as_deref(),\n    source_origin.as_deref(),\n);\nlet results: Vec<_> = results.into_iter().take(limit).collect();\n```\n\nAlso update the JSON response to include the new fields:\n\n```rust\njson!({\n    \"content\": r.entry.content,\n    \"score\": r.score,\n    \"source_file\": r.entry.metadata.source_file,\n    \"language\": r.entry.metadata.language,\n    \"content_role\": r.entry.metadata.content_role,\n    \"source_origin\": r.entry.metadata.source_origin,\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Update `tool_corvia_write` to accept and store new metadata**\n\nIn `tool_corvia_write` (mcp.rs ~line 677), read the new args and set on the entry's metadata:\n\n```rust\nlet content_role = args.get(\"content_role\").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).map(String::from);\nlet source_origin = args.get(\"source_origin\").and_then(|v| v.as_str()).map(String::from);\n\n// When building the entry, set metadata:\nentry.metadata.content_role = content_role;\nentry.metadata.source_origin = source_origin.or(Some(\"workspace\".into())); // default per spec\n```\n\nAlso update the write response to echo back the stored fields.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: Build and run server tests**\n\nRun: `cd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo build -p corvia-server && cargo test -p corvia-server`\nExpected: Compiles and tests pass\n\n- [ ] **Step 6: Commit**\n\n```bash\ncd /workspaces/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia\ngit add crates/corvia-server/src/mcp.rs\ngit commit -m \"feat(server): add content_role/source_origin filters to MCP search and write tools\"\n```\n\n---\n",
